Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Script cannot find credentials

Verify JSON files are properly formatted
Check regex patterns match credential formats
Ensure file paths are correct
Issue: API server not responding

Confirm server is running: ps aux | grep mock_api
Check port 8080 is not in use: netstat -tuln | grep 8080
Restart server if needed
Issue: Authentication always fails

Verify credentials match server's VALID_TOKENS
Check header format (Bearer vs API key)
Examine server logs for error details
Conclusion
This lab demonstrated how credentials can be inadvertently exposed in development tools and configuration files. You learned to:

Identify common credential storage locations
Extract credentials using pattern matching
Test harvested credentials against target systems
Automate the complete attack chain
Security Recommendations:

Never store credentials in configuration files
Use environment variables or secret management systems
Implement credential rotation policies
Monitor for exposed credentials in repositories
Use tools like git-secrets to prevent commits with credentials
